Shawn Leas wrote:
> The benefit comes in things like snapshots, where you can preserve
> metadata at some point in time, basically having a readonly copy
> of the whole FS from time HH:SS.
The next LVM release will provide snapshots (though they are
not persistent yet). Since this is at the block level it should 
work with any file system.
